t;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.nathanbransford.com/2013/10/how-to-get-over-writers-block.html" target="_blank"&gt;How to get over writer's block&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.nathanbransford.com/2010/10/nanowrimo-boot-camp-goals-and-obstacles.html" target="_blank"&gt;Make sure your characters have goals and obstacles&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.nathanbransford.com/2009/03/on-conflict.html" target="_blank"&gt;All about conflict&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.nathanbransford.com/2010/09/seven-keys-to-writing-good-dialogue.html" target="_blank"&gt;Seven keys to writing good dialogue&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.nathanbransford.com/2010/05/what-makes-great-setting.html" target="_blank"&gt;What makes a great setting&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.nathanbransford.com/2008/06/do-you-have-plot.html" target="_blank"&gt;Do you have a plot?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.nathanbransford.com/2011/11/five-ways-to-stay-motivated-while.html" target="_blank"&gt;Five ways to stay motivated&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.nathanbransford.com/2011/08/solution-to-every-writing-problem-that.html" target="_blank"&gt;The solution to every writing problem that has ever existed&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://blog.nathanbransford.com/2009/06/writing-advice-database.html" target="_blank"&gt;Writing Advice Database&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Good luck!!&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
